sequenceDiagram
  %% PROPOSED R1 sequence; acknowledgement semantics require an MQTT-client/QoS ADR.
  participant S as Source registry
  participant V as Credential vault
  participant B as MQTT broker
  participant I as Ingestion worker
  participant Q as Quarantine/DLQ
  participant D as Durable store/outbox
  participant M as Metrics/audit
  I->>S: authorize source, site, subscription
  S-->>I: credential reference + QoS/topic policy
  I->>V: retrieve credential by reference
  V-->>I: short-lived connection material
  I->>B: connect and subscribe
  B-->>I: MQTT message
  I->>I: validate payload size and format
  alt malformed or oversized
    I->>Q: bounded evidence + rejection reason
    I->>M: quarantine metric and provenance event
    I-->>B: acknowledge only per approved QoS policy
  else valid
    I->>I: calculate message identity/idempotency key
    alt duplicate or redelivery
      I->>M: duplicate metric + provenance event
      I-->>B: acknowledge only per approved QoS policy
    else new observation
      I->>D: transaction/outbox: raw evidence, schema observation, stream upsert, audit
      alt database unavailable
        I->>Q: bounded retry/quarantine record
        I->>M: dependency-failure metric
        I-->>B: defer acknowledgement per approved QoS policy
      else persisted
        D-->>I: commit
        I->>M: ingestion metric + provenance event
        I-->>B: acknowledge per approved QoS policy
      end
    end
  end
  alt broker disconnect
    I->>M: disconnect metric
    I->>I: reconnect with bounded backoff and jitter
  else graceful shutdown
    I->>B: stop intake and complete/hand off bounded work
    I->>D: flush outbox or record recovery state
  end
